TypeSignature.Value: .class public interface auto ansi abstract DataLabel

Docs.summary: Represents the data label on a chart point or trendline.

remarks.para: On a series, the DataLabel object is a member of the collection. The DataLabels collection contains a DataLabel object for each point. For a series without definable points (such as an area series), the DataLabels collection contains a single DataLabel object.
Use DataLabels(), where is the data-label index number, to return a single DataLabel object.
Use the property to return the DataLabel object for a single point.
On a trendline, the property returns the text shown with the trendline. This can be the equation, the R-squared value, or both (if both are showing).

MemberSignature.Value: public: property double Left { double get(); void set(double value); };

Docs.summary: The distance, in points, from the left edge of the object to the left edge of column A (on a worksheet) or the left edge of the chart area (on a chart). Read/write Double.

remarks.para: If the window is maximized, this property returns a negative number that varies based on the width of the window border. Setting this property to 0 (zero) will make the window a tiny bit smaller than it would be if the application window were maximized. In other words, if this property is 0 (zero), the left border of the main Microsoft Excel window will just barely be visible on the screen.
